		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=135315"><span id=Scholar>Mythox</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br />28 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.60]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Mythox&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Like a lot of bards, I gave up throwing once I max'd the skill back in my mid levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;I just recently picked it back up tho.  A lot of raid level mobs we're fighting now have short range AEs or even AE Rampage, and being in melee range when those go off sucks.  Using <a href="HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=24028" target="akztarg">Shuriken of Eternity</a> I can easy park with the casters twisting mana and resists while chain throwing stars at the mob.  The shuriken throw insanely fast, like 1 a second and no they wont all hit since our skill cap is pretty low.. but enough land and crit that it adds up.  And any DPS is better than zero, which is what you contribute if you dont melee or die to some nasty AE when you do melee hehe.<br><br>They're also very handy for outdoor pulling.  If you get a long ranged thrown weapon like shuriken above or forged javalins, you can stop at max range on the weapon... throw... back off with selo's.  Often you'll be far enough away by the time the weapon actually hits, that you will only pull a single even thru mobs that should assist.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Roseroar<br></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
